Gourmet Impling
Released11 June 2007 (Update)
Combat level28
MembersYes
LocationPuro-Puro, Everywhere
ExamineAn impling gourmet. Mmmm, tasty.
Advanced data
NPC ID1637,1647

The Gourmet impling is an Impling that can be caught in the Impetuous Impulses minigame, and are located throughout Puro-Puro and Gielinor. It is caught with either a normal or magic butterfly net equipped and an empty Impling jar in the player's inventory with 28 Hunter, or 38 Hunter barehanded. Capturing a Gourmet impling will grant the player 22 (if caught on Puro-Puro) or 24 (if caught on Gielinor) Hunter experience.

When the gourmet impling is finally caught, the player can either free it from the Gourmet impling jar, which will leave an item behind, or trade it to Elnock Inquisitor for special items. The player can either get 3 Impling jars for one Gourmet impling or, with 3 Baby implings and 2 Young impling, can get a can of Imp repellent, or alternatively can trade 3 Gourmet implings with 2 Earth implings and an Essence impling to receive a magic butterfly net.

Loot[edit | edit source]

At current Grand Exchange prices, opening a gourmet impling jar gives 1,176 worth of loot, on average. This means opening gourmet impling jars marks an average profit of −3,521 per jar, however this does not include loot from clue scrolls.

On average, one would profit −88,035 to get an easy clue scroll from gourmet impling jars at current Grand Exchange prices, excluding the rewards from the completed Treasure Trails.

The following drop rates are provided by Jagex, unless otherwise specified.
